{
  "info": {
    "name": "DXC Intelligence Analytics Platform — Sprint 1 (Full Routing)",
    "description": "Collection complète — 3 routing targets selon l'architecture DXC.\n\n## Table de routing\n\n| Intent | routing_target | Agent |\n|---|---|---|\n| sql, aggregation, comparison, explanation | null (NLQ direct) | NLQ Agent |\n| prediction, anomaly | generic_predictive_agent | Generic Predictive Agent (AutoML) |\n| sector_analysis | sector_specific_agent | Agent Spécifique (Prompt Builder) |\n| dashboard, kpi_chart, insight | insight_agent | Insight Agent (KPI + Chart + Power BI) |\n\n## Ordre d'exécution\n1. Health Check\n2. Detect Sector (sauvegarder sector_context)\n3. NLQ Chat — Direct (NLQ répond)\n4. NLQ Chat — Routing × 3 agents\n5. Multi-User Sessions\n6. Reset Session\n7. Error Handling",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {"key": "base_url",       "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string"},
    {"key": "sector_context", "value": "",                      "type": "string"},
    {"key": "user_id",        "value": "user_demo_001",         "type": "string"}
  ],
  "item": [

    {
      "name": "0 — Health Check",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "0.1 API Status",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": "{{base_url}}/health",
            "description": "Vérifie que l'API est opérationnelle."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',         () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('status = ok',        () => pm.expect(b.status).to.eql('ok'));",
              "pm.test('model contains llama',() => pm.expect(b.model).to.include('llama'));",
              "pm.test('active_sessions',    () => pm.expect(b.active_sessions).to.be.a('number'));",
              "console.log('✅ API OK | Model:', b.model, '| Sessions:', b.active_sessions);"
            ]}
          }]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "1 — Detect Sector",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1.1 Transport — query précise",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/detect-sector",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_query\": \"améliorer l'expérience des passagers de l'aéroport de Casablanca\"\n}"},
            "description": "Query claire → Transport détecté.\nSauvegarde le sector_context pour les appels /chat."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',              () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('sector = transport',       () => pm.expect(b.sector).to.eql('transport'));",
              "pm.test('routing_target',           () => pm.expect(b.routing_target).to.eql('transport_agent'));",
              "pm.test('confidence >= 0.85',       () => pm.expect(b.confidence).to.be.at.least(0.85));",
              "pm.test('kpis count 3-5',           () => pm.expect(b.kpis.length).to.be.within(3,5));",
              "pm.test('recommended_charts',       () => pm.expect(b.recommended_charts).to.be.an('array'));",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('sector_context', JSON.stringify(b));",
              "console.log('✅ Transport | conf:', b.confidence, '| KPIs:', b.kpis.map(k=>k.name).join(', '));",
              "console.log('   → sector_context sauvegardé');"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "1.2 Transport — query ambiguë SANS colonnes (confiance basse)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/detect-sector",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_query\": \"améliorer l'expérience client\"\n}"},
            "description": "Query trop générique → confiance basse (<0.80)."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',              () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('confidence < 0.80',        () => pm.expect(b.confidence).to.be.below(0.80));",
              "pm.test('metadata_used = false',    () => pm.expect(b.metadata_used).to.be.false);",
              "console.log('⚠️  Ambiguous | sector:', b.sector, '| conf:', b.confidence);"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "1.3 Transport — query ambiguë AVEC colonnes (confiance haute)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/detect-sector",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_query\": \"améliorer l'expérience client\",\n  \"column_metadata\": [\n    {\"name\": \"flight_id\",        \"description\": \"Identifiant unique du vol\"},\n    {\"name\": \"delay_minutes\",    \"description\": \"Retard en minutes\", \"sample_values\": [\"0\",\"15\",\"45\"]},\n    {\"name\": \"route\",           \"description\": \"Route aérienne\",    \"sample_values\": [\"CMN-CDG\",\"CMN-MAD\"]},\n    {\"name\": \"passenger_count\", \"description\": \"Passagers à bord\"}\n  ]\n}"},
            "description": "Même query + colonnes → metadata_used=true, confiance >= 0.88."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',              () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('sector = transport',       () => pm.expect(b.sector).to.eql('transport'));",
              "pm.test('confidence >= 0.88',       () => pm.expect(b.confidence).to.be.at.least(0.88));",
              "pm.test('metadata_used = true',     () => pm.expect(b.metadata_used).to.be.true);",
              "pm.collectionVariables.set('sector_context', JSON.stringify(b));",
              "console.log('✅ Columns boost | conf:', b.confidence, '| metadata_used:', b.metadata_used);"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "1.4 Finance",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/detect-sector",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_query\": \"analyser la performance financière et réduire les risques de défaut de crédit\"\n}"}
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',              () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('sector = finance',         () => pm.expect(b.sector).to.eql('finance'));",
              "pm.test('routing = finance_agent',  () => pm.expect(b.routing_target).to.eql('finance_agent'));",
              "console.log('✅ Finance | KPIs:', b.kpis.map(k=>k.name).join(', '));"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "1.5 Manufacturing",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/detect-sector",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_query\": \"optimiser la ligne de production et réduire les défauts qualité en usine\"\n}"}
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                    () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('sector = manufacturing',         () => pm.expect(b.sector).to.eql('manufacturing'));",
              "pm.test('routing = manufacturing_agent',  () => pm.expect(b.routing_target).to.eql('manufacturing_agent'));",
              "console.log('✅ Manufacturing | KPIs:', b.kpis.map(k=>k.name).join(', '));"
            ]}
          }]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "2 — NLQ Chat — Direct (NLQ répond)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "2.1 Agrégation — retard moyen",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/chat",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"question\": \"Quel est le taux de retard moyen ce mois ?\",\n  \"sector_context\": {{sector_context}}\n}"},
            "description": "intent=aggregation → NLQ répond directement.\nAttendu : requires_orchestrator=false, routing_target=null, SQL généré."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                  () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('requires_orchestrator=false',  () => pm.expect(b.requires_orchestrator).to.be.false);",
              "pm.test('routing_target=null',          () => pm.expect(b.routing_target).to.be.null);",
              "pm.test('intent=aggregation',           () => pm.expect(b.intent).to.eql('aggregation'));",
              "pm.test('generated_query has SELECT',   () => pm.expect(b.generated_query).to.include('SELECT'));",
              "pm.test('history_length=1',             () => pm.expect(b.history_length).to.eql(1));",
              "console.log('✅ Direct | intent:', b.intent, '| SQL:', b.generated_query?.substring(0,50));"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "2.2 Comparaison — routes",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/chat",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"question\": \"Compare les performances CMN-CDG vs CMN-MAD en termes de retard\",\n  \"sector_context\": {{sector_context}}\n}"},
            "description": "intent=comparison → NLQ direct. history_length=2."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                  () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('requires_orchestrator=false',  () => pm.expect(b.requires_orchestrator).to.be.false);",
              "pm.test('intent=comparison',            () => pm.expect(b.intent).to.eql('comparison'));",
              "pm.test('history_length=2',             () => pm.expect(b.history_length).to.eql(2));",
              "console.log('✅ Comparison | history:', b.history_length);"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "2.3 Follow-up — question de suivi",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/chat",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"question\": \"Et pour la route CMN-LHR spécifiquement ?\",\n  \"sector_context\": {{sector_context}}\n}"},
            "description": "'Et pour CMN-LHR ?' = follow-up implicite. Intent Classifier détecte is_follow_up=true. history_length=3."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                  () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('requires_orchestrator=false',  () => pm.expect(b.requires_orchestrator).to.be.false);",
              "pm.test('history_length=3',             () => pm.expect(b.history_length).to.eql(3));",
              "console.log('✅ Follow-up | history:', b.history_length);"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "2.4 SQL — liste des vols annulés",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/chat",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"question\": \"Liste les 10 vols avec le plus grand retard ce mois\",\n  \"sector_context\": {{sector_context}},\n  \"data_profile\": {\n    \"row_count\": 1500,\n    \"columns\": [\"flight_id\",\"route\",\"departure_date\",\"delay_minutes\",\"gate\",\"status\"],\n    \"numeric_columns\": [\"delay_minutes\"],\n    \"categorical_columns\": [\"route\",\"gate\",\"status\"],\n    \"datetime_columns\": [\"departure_date\"],\n    \"missing_summary\": {\"gate\": 2.1},\n    \"quality_score\": 87.5\n  }\n}"},
            "description": "intent=sql avec data_profile. SQL doit utiliser les vrais noms de colonnes."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                  () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('requires_orchestrator=false',  () => pm.expect(b.requires_orchestrator).to.be.false);",
              "pm.test('intent=sql',                   () => pm.expect(b.intent).to.eql('sql'));",
              "pm.test('SQL uses real columns',         () => pm.expect(b.generated_query?.toLowerCase()).to.satisfy(",
              "  s => s && (s.includes('delay_minutes') || s.includes('flight_id'))",
              "));",
              "console.log('✅ SQL | query:', b.generated_query?.substring(0,60));"
            ]}
          }]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "3 — NLQ Chat — Routing Generic Predictive Agent",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "3.1 Prediction → generic_predictive_agent",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/chat",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"question\": \"Prédis le taux de retard moyen pour le mois prochain\",\n  \"sector_context\": {{sector_context}}\n}"},
            "description": "intent=prediction → requires_orchestrator=true.\n\nFlux :\n NLQ Layer → requires_orchestrator=true\n → Orchestrateur → Generic Predictive Agent\n    (Dataset Profiling → ML Task Detection → AutoML Pipelines\n     → Parallel Training → Model Evaluation → Best Model\n     → Continuous Fine Tuning → Prediction Output)\n\nhistory_length inchangé (pas sauvegardé)."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                        () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('requires_orchestrator = TRUE',       () => pm.expect(b.requires_orchestrator).to.be.true);",
              "pm.test('routing_target = generic_predictive',() => pm.expect(b.routing_target).to.eql('generic_predictive_agent'));",
              "pm.test('intent = prediction',                () => pm.expect(b.intent).to.eql('prediction'));",
              "pm.test('answer mentions ML/prédiction',      () => pm.expect(b.answer.toLowerCase()).to.satisfy(",
              "  s => s.includes('prédiction') || s.includes('ml') || s.includes('modèle') || s.includes('automl')",
              "));",
              "pm.test('history_length unchanged = 3',       () => pm.expect(b.history_length).to.eql(3));",
              "console.log('🔀 PREDICTION → generic_predictive_agent');",
              "console.log('   routing_target:', b.routing_target);",
              "console.log('   history:', b.history_length, '← inchangé');"
            ]}
          }]
        },
        {
          "name": "3.2 Anomaly → generic_predictive_agent",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/chat",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"question\": \"Détecte les vols avec un comportement anormal ce mois\",\n  \"sector_context\": {{sector_context}}\n}"},
            "description": "intent=anomaly → même routing_target que prediction.\n\nFlux :\n NLQ → Orchestrateur → Generic Predictive Agent\n (ML Task Detection → AutoML → anomaly detection)"
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                        () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('requires_orchestrator = TRUE',       () => pm.expect(b.requires_orchestrator).to.be.true);",
              "pm.test('routing_target = generic_predictive',() => pm.expect(b.routing_target).to.eql('generic_predictive_agent'));",
              "pm.test('intent = anomaly',                   () => pm.expect(b.intent).to.eql('anomaly'));",
              "console.log('🔀 ANOMALY → generic_predictive_agent');"
            ]}
          }]
        }
      ]
    },

    {
      "name": "4 — NLQ Chat — Routing Sector Specific Agent",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "4.1 Sector Analysis → sector_specific_agent",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST", "url": "{{base_url}}/chat",
            "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
            "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"user_id\": \"{{user_id}}\",\n  \"question\": \"Fais une analyse complète et approfondie des performances du secteur transport ce trimestre\",\n  \"sector_context\": {{sector_context}}\n}"},
            "description": "intent=sector_analysis → requires_orchestrator=true.\n\nFlux :\n NLQ → Orchestrateur → Agent Spécifique\n    (Sector Context → Sector Prompt Builder → LLM Call\n     → Sector Explanation Output)\n     + Sector Predictive Model → Sector Prediction Output\n\nUtilisé pour les rapports sectoriels complets, pas pour des questions simples."
          },
          "event": [{
            "listen": "test",
            "script": { "exec": [
              "pm.test('Status 200',                      () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
              "const b = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.test('requires_orchestrator = TRUE',     () => pm.expect(b.requires_orchestrator).to.be.true);",
              "pm.test('routing_target = sector_specific', () => pm.expect(b.routing_target).to.eql('sector_specific_agent'));",
              "pm.test('intent = sector_analysis',         () => pm.expect(b.intent).to.eql('sector_analysis'));",
              "pm.test('answer mentions agent/analyse',    () => pm.expect(b.answer.toLowerCase()).to.satisfy(",
              "  s => s.includes('agent') || s.includes('analyse') || s.includes('sector') || s.includes('prompt')",
              "));",
              "console.log('🔀 SECTOR ANALYSIS → sector_specific_agent');",
              "console.log('   routing_target:', b.routing_target);"
            ]}
          }]
        }
      ]
    },

